Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1929, the Hungarian writer Frigyes Karinthy\N1929年，匈牙利作家Frigyes Karinthy
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.33,0:00:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,wrote in his short story CHAINS\N在短篇小说锁链中写道
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.60,0:00:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that a person tries to reach a designated person he doesn't know\N一个人试图通过不超过五个的中间人
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.60,0:00:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,through no more than five intermediaries\N来联系一个指定的陌生人
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.46,0:00:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the origin of six degrees of separation\N这便是六度分隔理论的起源
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.40,0:00:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Small-world experiment 1960s\N在二十世纪六十年代的小世界实验中
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.46,0:00:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Stanley Milgram and other researchers\NStanley Milgram和其他研究者们
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.88,0:00:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,examining the average path length for social networks\N检定美国人均社交网络路径
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.00,0:00:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of people in the United States is around 6\N长度为六
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.48,0:00:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the experiment was not completely randomized and idealized\N然而，该实验的设定不够随机又不够理想
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.26,0:00:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It was not until 1998 that Duncan Watts and Steven Strogatz\N直到1998年，Duncan Watts和Steven Strogatz
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.95,0:00:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,published the first network model on the small-world phenomenon\N才发表了关于小世界现象的第一个网络模型
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.42,0:00:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And this mathematical model has since been applied\N而后来，这个数学模型
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.88,0:00:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in a wide range of different areas\N被广泛地应用在了不同的领域
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.35,0:00:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, it is much easier to test the model with social network datasets.\N如今，用社交网络数据集来测试该模型就容易多了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.04,0:01:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We seek to validate the small-world network properties of Twitter\N我们试图从网络科学出发
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.02,0:01:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,by analysing datasets from the its network\N通过对推特网络的数据集进行分析 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.02,0:01:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,from a network science perspective\N验证推特的小世界网络属性
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.71,0:01:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This will allow us design a simple recommendation algorithm\N从而利用小世界网络的特性
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.55,0:01:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that exploits the features of the small-world network\N设计一种简单的推荐算法
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.91,0:01:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to uncover more possibilities\N来挖掘更多的可能性
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.91,0:01:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,like people you might know\N比如可能认识的人
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.42,0:01:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, we can implement more valuable features\N进一步来说，我们可以
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.66,0:01:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,based on that great piece\N根据那篇大名鼎鼎的 弱联系的力量
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.13,0:01:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,THE STRENGTH OF WEEK TIES\N实现更多有价值的功能
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.33,0:01:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how will we begin our work?\N那么，我们将如何开始？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.42,0:01:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,First we need to download the dataset for this analysis\N首先我们需要下载本次所需数据集
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.35,0:01:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to the work of Hubert Wassner\N感谢Hubert Wassner的成果
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.37,0:01:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we can download it directly from the Kaggle website\N我们可以直接从Kaggle网站下载
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.26,0:01:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This dataset is over 400MB\N这个数据集有400多兆
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.77,0:01:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and contains more than 40,000 rows of data\N囊括了四万余行数据
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.15,0:01:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,including 10 columns of information such as users ID and followers ID\N包含用户ID，粉丝ID等10列信息
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.20,0:01:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They are selected because they tweeted on Twitter trending topics\N这些用户被选中是因为他们在推特热门话题里发了推
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.06,0:01:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,, In order to filter out spam and non-informative accounts\N为了过滤掉广告和低质账户
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.51,0:02:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the founder had selected users that have at least 100 followers and followings\N创建者将至少拥有100个粉丝和关注的用户筛选出来
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.73,0:02:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Next is Data Preprocessing\N接下来我们需要进行数据的预处理
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.51,0:02:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What we should do is to change the data format to some useful dictionaries\N我们应该做的是将数据格式改为一些有用的字典
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.20,0:02:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We will use several dictionary for further uses\N我们在之后应该就要用到这些字典了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.57,0:02:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we need to build relevant networks\N然后是建立相关的网络
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.06,0:02:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We intend to construct a directed graph A\N我们打算以用户ID为点
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.68,0:02:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with User IDs as points and the connection list of follower IDs as edges\N和粉丝ID的联系为边，构筑有向图A
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.08,0:02:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, keep the interrelated edges and construct the undirected graph B\N下一步，保留互关的边，构筑无向图B
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.22,0:02:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In the analysis of the network we believe that operations\N在对网络的分析中，我们认为
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.73,0:02:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,such as computing degrees and clustering are necessary and helpful.\N计算degree、聚类等操作是必要且有帮助的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.71,0:02:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,More important is the analysis of the strong and weak ties\N比较重要的是对强弱链接的分析
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.51,0:02:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and we initially propose this division\N我们初步提出了这个划分方式
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.75,0:02:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,As for undirected graph B\N而对于无向图B来说
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.82,0:02:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we might be able to find those CONNECTORS\N我们或许可以找到那些社牛
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.00,0:02:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,people who has large networks of contacts and friends\N那些人脉很广，朋友圈很大的人
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.64,0:03:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all we have for today\N这便是我们今天的内容了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.73,0:03:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and we hope you all have a good result\N希望大家都有一个好的成果
